Reflection
The real-world testing gap, while initially disappointing, is actually an important research finding. It demonstrates that having more training data (700 vs 20 videos per sign) improves test accuracy but doesn't automatically solve the generalisation problem to new signers and environments. This suggests that for practical deployment, either:
* Fine-tuning on target users may be necessary
* Different architectural approaches (like domain adaptation) should be explored
* Or the system should be designed with appropriate confidence thresholds
